            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ESomeone%20has%20called%20Elijah's%20journey%20the%20place%20called%20there.%20During%20the%20three%20and%20one-half%20years%20of%20drought%2C%20God%20always%20directed%20him%20to%20go%20there.%20God%20commanded%20a%20widow%20to%20feed%20him%20there%20(1%20Kings%2017%3A9).%20There%20is%20an%20exact%20place%20where%20God%20wants%20us%20to%20be%20so%20He%20can%20sustain%20and%20bless%20us.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeter%20found%20the%20place%20called%20there%20when%20he%20was%20obedient%20and%20went%20to%20the%20house%20of%20Cornelius.%20Peter%2C%20like%20Elijah%2C%20was%20instructed%20to%20go%20to%20the%20home%20of%20a%20Gentile.%20This%20was%20the%20opposite%20of%20what%20they%20had%20been%20taught%20in%20their%20Jewish%20upbringing.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20place%20called%20there%20may%20not%20be%20the%20place%20we%20would%20naturally%20choose.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20the%20place%20where%20there%20is%20the%20greatest%20hunger.%20A%20desperately%20hungry%20widow%20and%20a%20spiritually%20hungry%20centurion%20both%20received%20the%20blessing%20from%20a%20man%20of%20God%20directed%20to%20their%20homes.%20As%20someone%20once%20said%2C%20%22Where%20God%20guides%2C%20He%20provides.%22%20We%20must%20endeavor%20to%20always%20remain%20in%20the%20place%20called%20there.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
