            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Kings.15:25-17:24",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Kings%2015%3A25-17%3A24%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_25%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ENadab%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3ENadab%20son%20of%20Jeroboam%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Israel%20in%20the%20second%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20He%20reigned%20in%20Israel%20two%20years.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_26%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%20and%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20his%20father%2C%20continuing%20the%20sins%20that%20Jeroboam%20had%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_27%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Baasha%20son%20of%20Ahijah%2C%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Issachar%2C%20plotted%20against%20Nadab%20and%20assassinated%20him%20while%20he%20and%20the%20Israelite%20army%20were%20laying%20siege%20to%20the%20Philistine%20town%20of%20Gibbethon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_28%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EBaasha%20killed%20Nadab%20in%20the%20third%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah%2C%20and%20he%20became%20the%20next%20king%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_29%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20immediately%20slaughtered%20all%20the%20descendants%20of%20King%20Jeroboam%2C%20so%20that%20not%20one%20of%20the%20royal%20family%20was%20left%2C%20just%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20promised%20concerning%20Jeroboam%20by%20the%20prophet%20Ahijah%20from%20Shiloh.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_30%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20was%20done%20because%20Jeroboam%20had%20provoked%20the%20anger%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20by%20the%20sins%20he%20had%20committed%20and%20the%20sins%20he%20had%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_31%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Nadab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20and%20everything%20he%20did%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_32%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EBaasha%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20constant%20war%20between%20King%20Asa%20of%20Judah%20and%20King%20Baasha%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_33%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3EBaasha%20son%20of%20Ahijah%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20all%20Israel%20in%20the%20third%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20Baasha%20reigned%20in%20Tirzah%20twenty-four%20years.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_15_34%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2215%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20he%20did%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%20and%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20Jeroboam%2C%20continuing%20the%20sins%20that%20Jeroboam%20had%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20message%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20delivered%20to%20King%20Baasha%20by%20the%20prophet%20Jehu%20son%20of%20Hanani%3A%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20lifted%20you%20out%20of%20the%20dust%20to%20make%20you%20ruler%20of%20my%20people%20Israel%2C%20but%20you%20have%20followed%20the%20evil%20example%20of%20Jeroboam.%20You%20have%20provoked%20my%20anger%20by%20causing%20my%20people%20Israel%20to%20sin.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20now%20I%20will%20destroy%20you%20and%20your%20family%2C%20just%20as%20I%20destroyed%20the%20descendants%20of%20Jeroboam%20son%20of%20Nebat.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20members%20of%20Baasha%26%23x2019%3Bs%20family%20who%20die%20in%20the%20city%20will%20be%20eaten%20by%20dogs%2C%20and%20those%20who%20die%20in%20the%20field%20will%20be%20eaten%20by%20vultures.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Baasha%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20and%20the%20extent%20of%20his%20power%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Baasha%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20Tirzah.%20Then%20his%20son%20Elah%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20message%20from%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20against%20Baasha%20and%20his%20family%20came%20through%20the%20prophet%20Jehu%20son%20of%20Hanani.%20It%20was%20delivered%20because%20Baasha%20had%20done%20what%20was%20evil%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sight%20(just%20as%20the%20family%20of%20Jeroboam%20had%20done)%2C%20and%20also%20because%20Baasha%20had%20destroyed%20the%20family%20of%20Jeroboam.%20The%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anger%20was%20provoked%20by%20Baasha%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sins.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EElah%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EElah%20son%20of%20Baasha%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Israel%20in%20the%20twenty-sixth%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20He%20reigned%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Tirzah%20for%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Zimri%2C%20who%20commanded%20half%20of%20the%20royal%20chariots%2C%20made%20plans%20to%20kill%20him.%20One%20day%20in%20Tirzah%2C%20Elah%20was%20getting%20drunk%20at%20the%20home%20of%20Arza%2C%20the%20supervisor%20of%20the%20palace.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EZimri%20walked%20in%20and%20struck%20him%20down%20and%20killed%20him.%20This%20happened%20in%20the%20twenty-seventh%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah.%20Then%20Zimri%20became%20the%20next%20king.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EZimri%20immediately%20killed%20the%20entire%20royal%20family%20of%20Baasha%2C%20leaving%20him%20not%20even%20a%20single%20male%20child.%20He%20even%20destroyed%20distant%20relatives%20and%20friends.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Zimri%20destroyed%20the%20dynasty%20of%20Baasha%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20had%20promised%20through%20the%20prophet%20Jehu.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20happened%20because%20of%20all%20the%20sins%20Baasha%20and%20his%20son%20Elah%20had%20committed%2C%20and%20because%20of%20the%20sins%20they%20led%20Israel%20to%20commit.%20They%20provoked%20the%20anger%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20with%20their%20worthless%20idols.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Elah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20and%20everything%20he%20did%20are%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EZimri%20Rules%20in%20Israel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EZimri%20began%20to%20rule%20over%20Israel%20in%20the%20twenty-seventh%20year%20of%20King%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%20in%20Judah%2C%20but%20his%20reign%20in%20Tirzah%20lasted%20only%20seven%20days.%20The%20army%20of%20Israel%20was%20then%20attacking%20the%20Philistine%20town%20of%20Gibbethon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20they%20heard%20that%20Zimri%20had%20committed%20treason%20and%20had%20assassinated%20the%20king%2C%20that%20very%20day%20they%20chose%20Omri%2C%20commander%20of%20the%20army%2C%20as%20the%20new%20king%20of%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Omri%20led%20the%20entire%20army%20of%20Israel%20up%20from%20Gibbethon%20to%20attack%20Tirzah%2C%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20capital.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs1_16_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs1%22%20ch%3D%2216%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Zimri%20saw%20that%20the%20city%20had%20been%20taken%2C%20he%20went%20into%20the%20citadel